From c56de483093d7ad0782327f95dda7da97bc4c315 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Miaoqian Lin <linmq006@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 12 May 2022 16:19:50 +0400
Subject: [PATCH] drm/msm/a6xx: Fix refcount leak in a6xx_gpu_init
Git-commit: c56de483093d7ad0782327f95dda7da97bc4c315
Patch-mainline: v5.19-rc1
References: git-fixes CVE-2022-49462 bsc#1238123

of_parse_phandle() returns a node pointer with refcount
incremented, we should use of_node_put() on it when not need anymore.

a6xx_gmu_init() passes the node to of_find_device_by_node()
and of_dma_configure(), of_find_device_by_node() will takes its
reference, of_dma_configure() doesn't need the node after usage.

Add missing of_node_put() to avoid refcount leak.

Fixes: 4b565ca5a2cb ("drm/msm: Add A6XX device support")
Signed-off-by: Miaoqian Lin <linmq006@gmail.com>
Reviewed-by: Akhil P Oommen <quic_akhilpo@quicinc.com>
Link: https://lore.kernel.org/r/20220512121955.56937-1-linmq006@gmail.com
Signed-off-by: Rob Clark <robdclark@chromium.org>
Acked-by: Takashi Iwai <tiwai@suse.de>

---
 drivers/gpu/drm/msm/adreno/a6xx_gpu.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/msm/adreno/a6xx_gpu.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/msm/adreno/a6xx_gpu.c
index 841e47a0b06b..caae816363d3 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/msm/adreno/a6xx_gpu.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/msm/adreno/a6xx_gpu.c
@@ -1914,6 +1914,7 @@ struct msm_gpu *a6xx_gpu_init(struct drm_device *dev)
 	BUG_ON(!node);
 
 	ret = a6xx_gmu_init(a6xx_gpu, node);
+	of_node_put(node);
 	if (ret) {
 		a6xx_destroy(&(a6xx_gpu->base.base));
 		return ERR_PTR(ret);
